event.descr:
The appliance has detected that the power on/off control signal (RS232C - DCD signal) is high on a serial port indicating that the server attached to the port is powered on. This trap is sent on initialization if the condition is detected. Subsequent traps occur only if there is a transition of the DCD signal from low to high. The affected serial port number is contained in cyAcsTrapObjectSerialPort. The affected serial port name is contained in cyAcsTrapObjectSerialPortName.

cyAcsTrapObjectSerialPort %parm[#2]%;
